OL,6,FHe added: "What I am proposing is a
OL,7,Fsensible pattern and solution.
OL,9,F"During the winter and Christmas
OL,10,Fperiod, when the weather is at its
OL,11,Fworst and the lights need to go up,
OL,12,Fflags come down in those particular
OL,13,Flocations.
OL,15,F"Then, in the New Year, residents are
OL,16,Fencouraged to put their flags back up
OL,17,F- fresh, tidy and in good condition.
OL,19,F"That was we honour our flags
OL,20,Fproperly, rather than leaving them to
OL,21,Frot."
